description: For sale: $249,900. Welcome home to this spacious END UNIT town home! Tons of natural light enters through three sides of windows. Home flow beautifully from the large entryway, to the giant living room and well lit kitchen with multiple spots to eat and entertain. Breakfast bar and dining areas are perfect for the space and there is a large deck right off the kitchen to entertain and enjoy grilling season. Three bedrooms and cute laundry room all on one level. Spacious and light filled bedrooms, along with a master that has its own full bathroom! Dont miss the huge storage space through the door on the back wall of the garage. NEW water heater 2016, NEW front steps 2019, NEW kitchen faucet 2020. Association will also be refinishing deck in Spring of 2020. Fantastic location near tons of shopping, grocery stores, restaurants, and public transportation. Walk to the Como Zoo and the State Fair every year and never pay for parking again! This one will go fast! Schedule your showing today!

description: For sale: $449,900. Turn of the century hilltop home located in sought after St. Anthony Park! 4 good-size bedrooms on upper level, 3 baths and over 2, 000 above ground finished square feet. Newer windows throughout entire house, as well as all porches. Beautiful maple floors run throughout the main and upper level. The sunny living room is lined with windows that showcase hilltop views and the adjoining dining room is perfect for entertaining. The professionally finished lower level includes a cozy family room, spacious laundry room and mudroom with ample closet space. There are 3 porches and an upper level deck overlooking the immense and beautiful back yard. The 23x14 garage top deck is the perfect spot for taking in the Minneapolis skyline and sunsets. Conveniently located between the St. Paul and Minneapolis U of M campus. Walk to Como Ave shops and restaurants. This home has been well cared for by the same owners for over 50 years.

description:
For sale: $225,000. Rare Duluth floor plan at Coffman on ground level with patio. 55+ active community of mostly former
University of Minnesota faculty and staff. Centrally located with quick access to both downtown St. Paul
and Minneapolis. Neighbors include Bell Museum and Les Bolstad golf course. Association amenities
include dinning facilities, library, community garden, patio, and court yard.

Recently sold: $405,000. Designed and totally rebuilt in 2001 by Architect Mark Gunstad according to the philosophy of the "Not So Big" House. This is the perfect home for a Couple, a Single Person or Downsizers who want to Garden, who do not want to live in a Condo, and who want to be in a charming, highly desirable, walkable, well-located neighborhood such as St. Anthony Park. Beautiful details in the wood, metal, tile and lighting throughout. House has 2 BR, 2 BA, separate DR, hardwood floors, Siematic Cabinetry in the Kitchen, many many windows and in the Lower Level, a Techline Deck system, Murphy Bed, and lots of Storage. There is a large Deck off the Kitchen, a wonderful Garden, carefully curated (see drawing in Supplements), Bluestone pathways. This house is a jewel and has been widely published.

Recently sold: $115,000. 732 Sq Ft. 1 bedroom Condo with Balcony overlooking Courtyard
MacLaren Hills is award winning Condominium building- Unique architecture as seen from Snelling Ave and Energy Park Drive

The Features...

"Energy park is a great place to live, especially if your condominium has a southeastern exposure to let the light flood into your home through the multiple windows and the full glass patio door. This cozy 1 bedroom condominium greets you with a spacious foyer and large coat closet. Beyond, there is a fully equipped kitchen (all appliances included) which open to a huge living area, which opens to your private patio deck. The bedroom is good size, and features a larges clothes closet. The bathroom is a very pleasant surprise, offering a large whirlpool style tub, a 6' vanity, and a linen closet. Also, please note the association fee INCLUDES HEAT.

The hassle-free lifestyle of condominium ownership is at its best at the MacLaren Hill Condominiums, which you will truly appreciate only after you have pulled your car in to the safe, secure underground parking garage, taken the elevator to your floor, and enjoyed the fact that your own home is just a few steps down the hall. The hallways, by the way, are one of the significant points of interest of these lovely homes, with spacious walkway, soaring ceiling, and generous lobby area."

In addition, this location is very close to Como Park, and Saint Paul Saints stadium. Bus lines run to either downtown, 15-20 minutes to downtown St. Paul, a little longer to downtown Minneapolis. New kitchen floor, new windows, new kitchen and bathroom faucets, and new dryer. Washer and Dryer are installed. Underground parking, has a very spacious locker (I have two bicycles, snowboard, camping equipment, and Xmas stuff in there, lots of storage in this locker).  The atrium was just painted last month, and new carpet is being installed this week. Association fee is $245/month, includes heat and a/c, and insurance.

description:
Recently sold: $501,000. Perfectly located near Langford Park and St. Anthony Park Elementary, near some of the most historic homes in the area, this vintage home will delight all!
	Wide steps and sidewalk lead you atop a small hill to this gem.  You are greeted by a large front Porch, a great place to watch the world go by.
	Stepping inside, there are gleaming hardwood floors, leaded glass windows, and several built ins, including a window seat in this huge Living Room.
	Continuing on you will find a main floor Bedroom, something not often found in this vintage home.  Better yet there is even a main floor Bathroom, newly redone.  
	In the rear of this home you find a huge Dining Area with more built ins.  Large windows overlook the lush rear yard.  Steps from the yard lead you to the school and Park beyond.  Off of this room is another Porch.
	The Kitchen is the center of this home.  It is not so large but extremely efficient.  One can easily see how it might be expanded and opened up.
	Now upstairs, where there are three generous sized Bedrooms.  The Den is full of wonderful built ins.  There is also another Bathroom up here.
	Downstairs you will find plenty of space for storage or puttering and a Rec Room.
	Inside..Outside...Truly a house you?ll want to call home!
